= TTF_RenderGlyph_LCD =

Create a 32-bit surface (SDL_PIXELFORMAT_ARGB8888) and render the given text using FreeType LCD rendering, with the given font and colors.

== Syntax ==

<syntaxhighlight lang='c'>
SDL_Surface * TTF_RenderGlyph_LCD(TTF_Font *font,
                Uint16 ch, SDL_Color fg, SDL_Color bg);
</syntaxhighlight>

== Function Parameters ==

{|
|'''font'''
|[[TTF_Font]] handle
|-
|'''ch'''
|character index
|-
|'''fg'''
|foreground color
|-
|'''bg'''
|background color
|}

== Return Value ==

Returns the new surface, or NULL if there was an error.

== Remarks ==

The glyph is rendered without any padding or centering in the X direction,
and aligned normally in the Y direction. This function returns the new
surface, or NULL if there was an error.

